@chopard @diormakeup @jeanpaulgaultier Video @samvissermakeup 

I am once again honored to share a room with some of the most genius beings on the planet! I do not take this opportunity lightly - and I am just grateful to watch and learn about the arts on a first basis level. I Love you @chopard , thank you for having me walk the carpet for you! This is the greatest education of films for a girl to be blessed with. Thank you🖤

node.text:
📽🫀🧜🏽‍♀️🌎🤍
Oh!! In my wildest dreams this came true!! Somebody pinch me! 

It's been 6 years since @jpgaultierofficial launched a ready to wear collection. It is my honor, with much love and respect, to represent a brand like JPG. Especially side by side with my fellow Palestinian brother @qaherhar and the epic, and endlessly coooollll @sesay_omar .

 I will never forget this moment of shooting with you @qaherhar . It is rare in this industry to get the privilege of having so much Palestine on one job, and our connection was immediate! Weve just got that Falasteeeen energy. Thank you @_hlsa_ for bringing us together. We love you ! 

To work on projects like this, with a team of people coming from all walks of life, is the reason I continue to do this job. To highlight the beauty in diversity and then to watch it shine so bright…. Well, it just made me really proud. 

Thank you to this incredible team. I send my love to you over and over again. You are all a dream, to me. 

“Les Marins” by @charlottemwales 
styling: @georgia.pendlebury 
Hair: @yann_turchi 
Makeup: @cecileparavina 
BTS: @taqwabintali 
Nails: @lilicreuk 
Set design: @Julien_ca
ENERGY @kohlerparis <3

BY @florencetetier 

Congratulations and thank you to @antoinegagey and the entire team. I Love you x a billion ! Every single one of you!

node.text:
Daydreaming of sunny New York City days with my latest campaign for @MichaelKors, inspired by Diana Vreeland’s famous saying “The Eye Has To Travel.” 👁 

Shot by the incredibly vibrant, Fun and kind director/ person , the one and only @mattypcock !!!!! 

STYLED BY THE @luxurylaw 
Hair and makeup by @tinadidit @kristimatamoros 

We were able to lock down the whole Museum  of Natural History to ourselves, take a boat around the Statue of Liberty, float through Central Park (I always stop at my favorite ice cream truck) and eat with my girls @mayowanicholas & @hello_kijeong which was one of the most memorable days !! Veryyyy “Night at the Museum” .... matty and I have a lot of BTS pictures... do you guys wanna see!?

Thank you Michael ❤️

3/3 (Sorry - Just PASSIONATE!!) 😂
Anywayssss…. 

At one point or another, especially during quarantine, we all felt just BLEH. Completely unmotivated, anti-social, depressed, anxious, following with the attack of the “sleepy brain” This is the reason I felt the WORLD deserves to try KIN and to feel HAPPY. YOU deserve to feel happy! 
 
Kin is the first drink to use adaptogens and focus on brain health, while expanding our mind and calming our nervous system. 
 
Throughout my whole life, I have only wanted to promote products and business’ that I wholeheartedly stand by. If it feels unauthentic to me, it’s hard for me to do what I do best.  That’s why I am so passionate about sharing with you my newest endeavor, so we can help bring happiness back into the world, through brain health. 
 
What I believe is that Kin makes you want to be social. Kin makes you feel grounded. Kin makes you want to dance. Kin makes you want to smile. Kin makes you want to talk. Kin makes you want to chill. Kin makes you want to feel your best. Kin makes you want to do what you do best. Kin makes you feel happy to be alive. At all times. With no sacrifices. 
 
“ITS NOT A BUZZ, ITS BLISS”

BRAIN POWER BEV FROM THE FUTURE.

node.text:
(2/3) This is THE drink to make you feel good. Before anything, I was a passionate consumer. It has benefited me for over a year now, with ingredients that help calm our nervous system, add serotonin to our brains, center us, ground us, and energize without the crash! 
 
Trying Kin for the first time was one of the most life changing moments for me. 3 days later, I personally called Jen to see who was the genius behind “euphorics.” I had already been taking Gabba and Tyrosine for my anxiety, and to come across this cute, tiny drink, already using those exact ingredients, made my heart jump. I just knew, I needed to help spread this message and work hand in hand with Jen to make the greatest mood enhancing drink of all time! 
 
The reason why I am coming on with Kin, is not only to consistently give you new formulas, creatives and products, but to also teach you about brain health and how we can help with the social, personal, physical, and mental pressures we face on a regular basis. 
 
Kin is a non-alcoholic product, including Gaba, a naturally-occurring nootropic chemical that promotes relaxation, Tyrosine, a mood enhancer, rhodiola rosea, which induces euphoria and helps with hormone harmony. 
 
what more could you need!? 

The “ euphoric” feeling of drinking, without the hangover, the guilt, or the long term effect. Kin is constantly building your brain to be the best version of itself, while making you feel great in the process. @kineuphorics @jenofkin

node.text:
"CREATION IS MY LOVE LANGUAGE” and the fact that i get to do it with my kindered spirit, soul sister, @jenofkin is one of the most magical parts! 

I am officially the Co-Founder, Partner and COO, of our baby… @KinEuphorics 

As Jen would say, we are the first braincare beverage & the first drink to sit boldly at the intersection of feeling good & living well. science + magic. 🔅🔆
 
No matter who you are, or what you do, Kin is for you. Kin is for the busy, multi-tasker. Kin is for the chiller. The artist. The writer. The wall street business hu-man, the college student, the mother, the stay at home father, the creatives, the hard worker of any form. People universally will benefit from Kin. Once you try it, you just know. 
 
Whether you are sober, trying to cut down, or just want something to mix with, Kin will be the first to bring brain care to the bar. 
 
As many of you know, I have suffered from extreme depression and anxiety for most of my teenage and adult life. Since I was 14, I had tried everything to help myself feel better. After years of social drinking at work event after work event, along with suffering from different immune problems as well, my body started to tell me “NO". I wasn’t able to go out anymore with the work schedule I had. My social anxiety was something that slowly crept up on me as I grew into my twenties. It got harder for me to go out without having one drink to calm my nerves,  which made me not want to go out at all, so I was just hibernating between jobs.  With a life that is constantly pushing a social regime, along with working 13 hour days, every single day, I knew this wasn’t a sustainable life for me. So I searched and scoured for anything holistic that would help with my chronic exhaustion, depression  and anxiety. Asking myself and the universe that maybe since I had been so lucky in other aspects of my life, that this low vibration was just where I would have to stay. Until the universe brought me to Jen and KIN! (1/2)
